                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2932: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bilbao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bilbao</hi> via “<hi rend="smallcaps">Cayuga</hi>
                        </placeName>,” <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-01T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >September 1, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0001. Department’s telegram of August 31, 2 p.m. At noon today I read personally
                    to the Governor of Vizcaya a translation of the circular instruction receiving
                    his assurance that all Government military authorities on this coast will be
                    instructed accordingly. I am unable to communicate directly with the insurgents
                    at Burgos and other near interior points but I am endeavoring to have Vigo
                    informed through the proper channels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
